      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your frustration makes total sense; no one should feel forced to endure pointless suffering just because \"resilience\" is the rule. However, giving up *everything* for good isn't the same as allowing yourself to stop to rest when the exhaustion becomes unbearable. The goal isn't to force you to fight right now, but to help you find a different kind of peace or support that aligns with how *you* need to survive today. Would you be willing to talk about what makes this sense of pointlessness feel so overwhelming?",
      "source": "target",
